snippet.title: How To Build A Shelf Between Two Walls
snippet.description:
Here‚Äôs the fastest and easiest way to build a shelf between two walls.
Using a level, I mark a line on all three walls at the bottom of the shelf.
And yes- a laser would work great for this, but I want to show how you can do basic jobs with simple tools.
Next, I measure the depth of the shelves and cut two cleats out of 2x4s- I left room to add a face board later.
Then I cut 4 more 2x4s to run between the cleats, making a ladder wall.
Three-inch deck screws work great for jobs like this- I put two per stud.
It‚Äôs important to measure the width of the shelf at the back wall and at the front because it can vary.
I screw the frame to the wall making sure to hit studs- that‚Äôs not going anywhere.
Now let‚Äôs cut the plywood- no fancy track saw, no problem. Just clamp down a straight board to use as a guide.
After dry fitting the plywood, I could see there was a bulge on the side wall keeping the shelf from sliding all the way back.
So, I use my pencil like a scribe, now I can cut the plywood to fit the wall.
I apply liquid nails to the frame and set the shelf down- fits like a glove.
Next, I load 1 ¬æ‚Äù trim nails into my 15-gauge trim gun to shoot it down.
I measure with a tape- making sure to hit the frame.
When I cut the face board, I use a 2-degree bevel, this way it‚Äôs a little longer in the front than the back and makes it fit super snug (you can see here what a good fit I got).
Don‚Äôt worry -The nail holes get filled before it‚Äôs painted.
At this point I was so tired I decided to take a nap.
And then, the New Guy actually came out of his office to paint it for me.
Be sure to like and follow (subscribe) for more content like this. @hausplans

#build #howto #carpentry #framing #construction #diy #contractor #tools

snippet.title: Stevie Nicks on speaking out
snippet.description:
Stevie Nicks became a superstar as lead singer and songwriter for the '70s band Fleetwood Mac, and a platinum-selling solo artist. She talks with correspondent Tracy Smith about composing her latest song, "The Lighthouse," that was inspired by her own experience with abortion, and a strong desire to "do something" following the Supreme Court decision overturning Roe v. Wade. She also discusses the loss of her bandmate Christine McVie in 2022, and how she continues to pay tribute to her.

snippet.title: Wild Life: Episode 2 - EATING WELL!
snippet.description:
Wild Life: Episode 2 - EATING WELL! Session 2, all food is 100% randomised... with everything being edible. 

This season, we have 6 lives. 4-6 Lives you have a dark green name. 3 lives you have a lime green name. 2 lives you have a yellow name and on your last and final life, you turn hostile and red. The last player standing, wins. Dark green names are able to have lives stolen from them when killed by a red or yellow life. Only Red names can kill anyone. 

There are lots of little details to be revealed as the series goes on. 

Enjoy!

snippet.title: The True Scale Of Modern Nuclear Weapons
snippet.description:
The terrifying true scale of modern nuclear weapons is beyond what most people can imagine. Nuclear Weapons today are far more powerful than those used in World War II. For example, the B83 nuclear bomb, the largest in the U.S. arsenal, is 80 times more powerful than the bomb dropped on Hiroshima. This single Nuclear Weapon could destroy an entire city like Beijing, causing millions of deaths and injuries.

Submarine-launched missiles like the Trident II carry multiple Nuclear Weapons. Each missile can deliver up to eight warheads, each 30 times more powerful than the Hiroshima bomb. A single Trident II could devastate a city like Moscow, resulting in over 2.8 million immediate fatalities.

China's Dongfeng 5 missile is another example of the terrifying power of Nuclear Weapons. It can carry up to 12 warheads, each 66 times more powerful than the Hiroshima bomb. If aimed at a city like Washington, D.C., the impact would be catastrophic, with over a million fatalities.

Russia's R-36 missile, known as the "Satan" missile, can carry multiple Nuclear Weapons with immense destructive power. Some versions can deliver a single warhead up to 20 megatons, which is over 1,300 times the Hiroshima bomb.

At the top of the list is Russia's RS-28 Sarmat missile, nicknamed "Satan 2." This Nuclear Weapon can carry up to 15 warheads and potentially deliver a 50-megaton bomb, causing unimaginable destruction to cities like New York.

Even though some countries may face setbacks, the existence of these Nuclear Weapons means that even a few could cause unimaginable damage. The true scale of modern Nuclear Weapons shows that in a nuclear war, there are no winners‚Äîonly devastating loss for humanity.

Sources:

https://nuclearsecrecy.com/nukemap/
U.S. Department of Energy https://www.energy.gov/
National Museum of the U.S. Air Force https://www.nationalmuseum.af.mil/
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nuclear_weapon

snippet.title: Blood Sweat & Tears | Official Music Video - League of Legends
snippet.description:
Wounded and near death, Ambessa sees a vision of what awaits her as a follower of the Wolf. 
Join the hunt on Nov 6, 2024 with Ambessa and the Chosen of the Wolf skinline.

Created in partnership with Fortiche.

LISTEN NOW: https://arcane.lnk.to/bloodsweatandtears 

MUSIC CREDITS
Performed by: Sheryl Lee Ralph
Writers: Rose Betts, Ester Dean, Tanguy Destable, Yoann Lemoine (Woodkid), Alex Seaver, Charlie Trimbur
Produced by: Alex Seaver, Yoann Limoine (Woodkid), Tanguy Destable, Bill Hemstapat
Ambessa Choir:
Danielle Withers
Angie Fisher
Toni Scruggs
Windy Wagner
Ayo Awosika
Amy Keys
Brandon Winbush
Gregory Fletcher
Suzanne Waters
Vocals recorded by: Alisse Laymac at The Village Studios
Choir Recorded by: Adam Michalak at Hollywood Scoring
Mixed by Chris Tabron
Mastered by Joe LaPorta at Sterling Sound
Creative Lead: Kiahna Manker
Music Project Manager: Kerianne Pinkstaff
Additional Production Support: Hollywood Scoring
Executive Producer: Christian Linke

LYRICS
I was raised by wolves
I was born to lead
And I starve ‚Äôtil there‚Äôs no more mouths to feed
There‚Äôs a hand on my throat
And a blade at my feet
But the weight of the world won‚Äôt bend my knees

Broken bones, battle scars
I have seen the bloodshed
Carved in stone, when it‚Äôs my sword
They won‚Äôt forget

No war, no peace
‚ÄôTill I lead them all
Leave me with my demons
Hear my voice call
No fears or sorrows underneath these bones
Just blood, sweat and tears
Is all I know
I can use who I want
And I taste what I please
In this world I get all my fantasies
There‚Äôs a hand on my throat
And a child at my feet
But the weight of the world won‚Äôt bend my knees
No war, no peace
‚ÄôTill I lead them all
Leave me with my demons
Hear my voice call
No fears or sorrows underneath these bones
Just blood, sweat and tears
Is all I know
[Don‚Äôt wash away my Blood, don‚Äôt wash away my Sweat, don‚Äôt wash away my Tears]
Don‚Äôt wash my spirit, don‚Äôt cleanse my soul
Can‚Äôt break my courage, and I won‚Äôt fall
‚ÄôCause that‚Äôs all I know
No war, no peace
‚ÄôTill I lead them all
Leave me with my demons
Hear my voice call
No fears or sorrows underneath these bones
Just blood, sweat and tears
Is all I know

Is all I know

Hear my voice call

Just blood, sweat and tears
Is all I know

snippet.description:
Los Angeles Lakers defeats Sacramento Kings, 131-127. For Los Angeles, Lebron James recorded his 113th career triple-double and led the way with 32 points (4 3PM), 14 rebounds, and 10 assists while Anthony Davis (31 points, 9 rebounds, 3 steals, 2 assists), Rui Hachimura (18 points, 9 rebounds), and Austin Reaves (16 points, 7 rebounds, 6 assists) combined for 65 points the victory. Domantas Sabonis finished with 29 points, 12 rebounds, and 10 assists while De‚ÄôAaron Fox tallied 28 points (3 3PM), 5 rebounds, and 10 assists for Sacramento. The Lakers improve to 3-0 on the season, while the Kings fall to 0-2.

Domantas Sabonis notches his 59th career triple double, tying Larry Bird for 10th most in NBA history

LeBron James notches his 11th 30 PT triple double as a Laker, passing Elgin Baylor for 2nd most in Lakers franchise history. He now trails only Magic Johnson (30 such games)

snippet.title: SUNS at LAKERS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | October 25, 2024
snippet.description:
Never miss a moment with the latest news, trending stories and highlights to bring you closer to your favorite players and teams.
Download now: https://link.nba.com/NBAYouTube

Los Angeles Lakers defeats Phoenix Suns, 123-116. For Los Angeles, Anthony Davis led the way with 35 points, 8 rebounds, 4 assists, and 2 blocks while aided by Austin Reaves (26 points (5 3PM), 4 rebounds, 8 assists, 3 steals) and Lebron James (21 points, 4 rebounds, 8 assists) in the victory. Kevin Durant finished with 30 points, 4 rebounds, and 6 assists while Devin Booker has tallied 23 points (4 3PM) and 4 assists for Phoenix in the losing effort. The Lakers improve to 2-0 on the season, while the Suns fall to 1-1.
With 35 PTS tonight, Anthony Davis becomes the first Laker to record 30+ PTS in back-to-back games to start the season since Kobe Bryant in 2005.
First time since 2010-11, that the Lakers start season 2-0.

A natural talent, Quando Rondo was once a small child, secretly singing in the bathroom as a 9-year-old boy in Savannah, GA. His natural gravitation towards music lead to him to hip-hop; he began recording his fledgling verses on his cell phone. He quickly gained traction online, racking up millions of views on YouTube.

Fittingly, he titled his 2018 mixtape 'Life B4 Fame' with the hopes that things would change for the better once his career really took off. He was right‚Äîwithin two days, his mixtape had amassed more than one million streams on MyMixtapez. Things will only go up from there, and if the snippets from his forthcoming Rich Homie Quando project are any sign, he‚Äôs only only getting better with time.

#QuandoRondo #LifeGoesOn #hereforareason

snippet.title: ONE Squishy, THREE Makeovers
snippet.description:
ORDER THE ME GUIDEBOOK:  https://moriahelizabethmerch.com/

___UPLOAD SCHEDULE___

Friday at 4:00pm ET

___________WELCOME TO MY CHANNEL__________

Hey! my name is Moriah (pronounced muh-rye-yuh) Elizabeth and this is my channel....obviously. I'm 29 and like doing creative activities (mostly painting on things), or really anything that gives me an excuse to use rainbows, sprinkles and my own cutesy characters in excess. I'm heavy into editing, so my video are chalk full of sound effects, filters and lil....moments, or as we like to call them "MEmes." I paint on squishies, thrift store finds, and various other items I find. I also love to draw, traditionally and digitally. I'm not the most skilled artist out here, but I like to focus on having fun with creativity and being able to laugh at my own mistakes. 

CURRENT SERIES:
Squishy Makeovers: Fixing and decorating used squishies sent from my viewers
Thrift Store Makeovers: Fixing and decorating stuff I find at thrift stores/yard sales
Bake With ME: Recreating squishies I've decorated in real life
Create This Book: Drawing in the prompt book that I wrote (available to purchase and follow along)
Squishy Unboxing: Opening used squishy packages sent from viewers
Drawings to Squishies: turning my flat drawings into squishies
Finishing Art Ideas: Choosing art ideas from my giant list and making them happen
Squishies I've Been Avoiding: Painting on the squishies I DON'T want to paint

snippet.title: Is My Dog Alive?
snippet.description:
Burn Face and Scattered Skull have invaded HQ, and what's worse? They kidnapped Clue and are saying he isn't alive! They said they need him for DNA testing, but we can't let that happen. I take Vy, Shinobi, Stormi, and Reo to the Scattered Skull Safe House to get Burnface back at all costs, even though an army of initiates stands in our way! Will we get captured? Will we be able to save Clue in time? There's only one way to find out!

snippet.title: Dua Lipa: Tiny Desk Concert
snippet.description:
Stephen Thompson | October 25, 2024
When Dua Lipa came to visit the Tiny Desk, she had nothing to prove ‚Äî and much to live up to. After all, the singer‚Äôs Tiny Desk (home) concert, recorded in London in the aftermath of her 2020 blockbuster Future Nostalgia, still holds the record for the most-viewed Tiny Desk concert in history, her 130 million views surpassing even the likes of Mac Miller and Anderson .Paak. 

Four years later, the pop superstar finally graced the actual Tiny Desk, this time armed with four warm and inviting songs from Radical Optimism. Arriving in the first half of this year ‚Äî when the dominant storylines in music so often revolved around grievances and rivalries ‚Äî Radical Optimism stood out for its comparatively sunny and forgiving takes on failed and failing relationships, seduction, new love and old wounds. And, of course, it dispensed a world-beating banger in ‚ÄúHoudini,‚Äù which joins past Dua Lipa classics (‚ÄúNew Rules,‚Äù ‚ÄúLevitating,‚Äù ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt Start Now‚Äù) on her own personal Mount Rushmore.

Befitting an artist whose newest songs often reflect the pursuit of personal growth ‚Äî see: ‚ÄúHappy for You‚Äù ‚Äî Lipa and her team breezed through the NPR Music offices with a mix of low-drama professionalism and unmistakable warmth. We‚Äôve dealt with a lot of stars (and their teams) over the years, and as often as people ask us to dish about people who‚Äôve been difficult, we‚Äôve mostly accumulated stories of people who‚Äôve been lovely to have around. Even among all those, Lipa and her people stood out: They were kind, gracious, fun and game.

That shows up on camera, too, as you‚Äôll see here. This is joyful music, at a time when we could all use it.

‚ÄúThese Walls‚Äù
‚ÄúHappy for You‚Äù
‚ÄúHoudini‚Äù

snippet.title: Staying In Las Vegas‚Äô Infamous Luxor Resort (It Was Bad)
snippet.description:

Notably, and perhaps infamously, standing on the southern end of the Las Vegas strip, sits a casino like no other. It's the Luxor, a massive glass pyramid themed after Egypt and one which has been open since the early 1990's. But today, it's a poorly reviewed and ultra cheap resort. So I figured, let's try it out. This is my review of the Luxor Las Vegas, in the highest suite you can get within the iconic Pyramid!

snippet.title: Dominik Mysterio On Liv Morgan, Rhea Ripley, Eddie Guerrero, His "Deadbeat Dad" Rey Mysterio
snippet.description:
Dominik Mysterio is a professional wrestler with WWE. He sits down with Chris Van Vliet at Circa Resort and Casino in Las Vegas to talk about WrestleMania 41 tickets going on sale, his recent love triangle with Liv Morgan and Rhea Ripley, being the son of the legendary Rey Mysterio, his debut match against Seth Rollins at SummerSlam 2020, being CM Punk's first WWE match in 10 years, why he loves chicken tenders so much, his order at In-N-Out burger, being inspired by Eddie Guerrero, his epic mullet and much more!

BLUECHEW: Use the code CVV to get your first month of BlueChew for FREE at https://bluechew.com

04:50 Being CM Punk‚Äôs first match in WWE after his 10-year absence

snippet.title: 2 Minecraft Speedrunners VS TITAN
snippet.description:
2 Minecraft Speedrunners VS TITAN. You asked for it. The return of Minecraft Manhunt, George & Dream VS a real life Titan

Follow my socials:
‚ûΩ Twitter - @dream
‚ûΩ Instagram - @dreamwastaken
‚ûΩ Snapchat - @dreampublic

George: @GeorgeNotFound 

Merch: https://www.dream.shop

All video music is custom scored and produced by Dream & PmBata. 

We decided to call this series Minecraft Manhunt 2: TITAN TAKEDOWN. This video is a different rendition of it, where there is a massive, near invincible TITAN, being controlled by a real life human projected into the game using our custom fusion technology, instead of multiple hunters. This is the toughest challenge I have faced yet. GeorgeNotFound and I are on a team of 2, and are trying to speedrun and beat the game.

This is a new Minecraft but, 1.21 challenge that we have decided to try. I try to beat the game, while my anonymous friend tries everything he can to stop me. This is all custom coded by us. 

If this video somehow gets 1,000,000 likes we'll announce the date of the next episode early.

Not Minecraft, But Water Rises or Minecraft, But Lava Rises, or any other but challenge like that. This is a speed run / speed runner of Minecraft against a killer / assassin

#MinecraftManhunt #MinecraftManhunt2

snippet.title: SNEAK PEEK: Your First Look at The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills Season 14 | RHOBH | Bravo
snippet.description:
Will shifting group dynamics cause Kyle Richards to leave RHOBH behind for good? Watch the premiere of The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills, November 19 at 8/7c on Bravo and streaming next day on Peacock.

‚ñ∫‚ñ∫ WATCH FULL EPISODES NOW: https://bravo.app.link/Bravo-YT   
‚ñ∫‚ñ∫ VISIT BRAVO‚ÄôS OFFICIAL SITE: http://bravo.ly/Official
#Bravo #RHOBH #SneakPeek #DoritKemsley #KyleRichards

About The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills:
In the aftermath of last season‚Äôs turbulent ending, the women find themselves attempting to navigate their fractured friend group. When Dorit enlists a spiritual guru to help them find their way back, the ladies confront their issues head on and begin to mend hurt feelings.
 
Kyle is a diamond under pressure, struggling to cope amid her most challenging year yet. With her 27-year marriage in turmoil and her relationship with her sister in limbo, Kyle reaches her breaking point after the tabloids ‚Äì and those closest to her ‚Äì question her budding friendship with a well-known country singer. 
 
Southern socialite Sutton takes her professional life by the reins. Needing a bit of guidance in the romance department, however, she turns to one of Beverly Hills‚Äô top dating coaches to get to the bottom of her one-date woes. When Sutton takes Kyle to task over setbacks in their friendship, tensions among the group take a turn for the worse. 
 
A focused Erika eyes a career comeback, and she works to rebuild her life despite ongoing legal battles. Things are finally looking up when Erika lands herself a hard-earned Las Vegas residency, but bubbling self-doubt due to a four-year performance hiatus has her questioning whether she can pull it off. 
 
Garcelle has cracked the code to success in Hollywood. When one of her teenage boys unexpectedly confronts her over her parenting style, however, Garcelle finds herself in uncharted territory. Wondering if she‚Äôs doing it all wrong, she attempts to change her approach with both her sons. 
 
Dorit continues to deal with PTSD caused by her home invasion, which proves especially difficult after she‚Äôs robbed again. On top of this, she and PK attempt to work their way back from an issue that almost cost them their marriage.  
 
Crystal has found her voice within the group, holding her own after one of the women questions what she stands for. She soon finds she can‚Äôt win them all, however, when her need for control gets the best of her and threatens her relationship with her brother. 
 
Introduced to the group through her friend, Kyle, newcomer Annemarie is a force to be reckoned with. A certified registered nurse anesthetist who thrives under pressure and knows her facts, she‚Äôs not afraid to call out the women when they speak out of turn. Going head-to-head with Sutton and Crystal over a few questionable comments, she quickly finds her footing with the ladies. 

Garcelle Beauvais 
Erika Jayne
Dorit Kemsley
Bozoma Saint John
Kyle Richards
Sutton Stracke
Kathy Hilton
Jennifer Tilly

Bravo is the premier lifestyle and entertainment brand that drives cultural conversation around its high-quality, interactive original content across all platforms. The network has a diverse slate of original programming that includes unscripted favorites such as Emmy Award-winning ‚ÄúTop Chef‚Äù and ‚ÄúProject Runway,‚Äù ‚ÄúVanderpump Rules,‚Äù ‚ÄúBelow Deck,‚Äù ‚ÄúSouthern Charm,‚Äù and the popular ‚ÄúMillion Dollar Listing‚Äù and ‚ÄúThe Real Housewives‚Äù franchises. Bravo also boasts the only live late-night talk show on television with the critically acclaimed ‚ÄúWatch What Happens Live with Andy Cohen,‚Äù which has become a nightly destination for A-list celebrities.

snippet.title: Severance ‚Äî Season 2 Official Teaser | Apple TV+
snippet.description:
Things look a little different around Lumon.

Severance Season 2 premieres January 17 on Apple TV+ http://apple.co/_Severance

In Severance, Mark Scout (Adam Scott) leads a team at Lumon Industries, whose employees have undergone a severance procedure, which surgically divides their memories between their work and personal lives. This daring experiment in ‚Äúwork-life balance‚Äù is called into question as Mark finds himself at the center of an unraveling mystery that will force him to confront the true nature of his work‚Ä¶ and of himself.

In season two, Mark and his friends learn the dire consequences of trifling with the severance barrier, leading them further down a path of woe.

Season 2 reunites its ensemble cast of stars including Emmy Award nominee Adam Scott, Britt Lower, Tramell Tillman, Zach Cherry, Jen Tullock, Michael Chernus, Dichen Lachman, Emmy Award winner John Turturro, Academy Award winner Christopher Walken and Academy and Emmy Award winner Patricia Arquette, and welcomes new series regular Sarah Bock.

Severance is executive produced by Ben Stiller, who also directs five episodes this season in addition to directors Uta Bresiewitz, Sam Donovan and Jessica Lee Gagn√©. The series is written, created and executive produced by Dan Erickson. Severance season two is also executive produced by John Lesher, Jackie Cohn, Mark Friedman, Beau Willimon, Jordan Tappis, Sam Donovan, Caroline Baron, Richard Schwartz, Nicholas Weinstock. In addition to starring, Adam Scott and Patricia Arquette serve as executive producers. Fifth Season is the studio.

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS! Man City 5-0 Sparta Prague | Haaland wonder goal as super City hit five!
snippet.description:

Phil Foden took less than three minutes to fire us ahead with a neat finish before three goals in 10 second-half minutes saw City take control of the tie.

Erling Haaland scored twice, the first an audacious and acrobatic, head-high flicked volley, either side of John Stones‚Äô header, before Matheus Nunes‚Äô late penalty.

Welcome, hunters, to the third locale in the Forbidden Lands; the Oilwell Basin. Meet the people of Azuz, the Everforge, and come face-to-face with three of the area's new monstrous denizens, including the ominous Black Flame.

snippet.title: Murtazaliev vs Tszyu HIGHLIGHTS: October 19, 2024 | PBC on Prime Video
snippet.description:
Undefeated IBF Super Welterweight World Champion Bakhram Murtazaliev dropped former world champion Tim Tszyu four times on his way to a third-round stoppage in the main event of PBC Championship Boxing on Prime Video action Saturday night from the Caribe Royale Resort in Orlando, Florida.
 
After winning the title in his opponent‚Äôs home territory of Germany earlier this year, Murtazaliev (23-0, 17 KOs) made a statement by dropping Tszyu (24-2, 17 KOs) early and often on his way to the dominant stoppage.
 
The first knockdown came in round two with a strong counter left hook sending Tszyu to the canvas. Tszyu showed the incredible grit that‚Äôs made him a superstar in his native Australia to rise to his feet, but was ultimately sent back to the ground two more times in the round.
 
"We just worked on these combinations all the time and when the fight came, it was automatic,‚Äù said Murtazaliev. ‚ÄúWe worked for 10 weeks on those punches that hurt him. We created opportunities and we believed that we could win this fight.‚Äù
 
Continuing to press forward and look for moments in round three, Murtazaliev landed another vicious counter left hand that scored him his fourth knockdown in less than three rounds. While Tszyu continued to battle back, the onslaught from Murtazaliev proved to be too much as Tszyu‚Äôs corner threw in the towel, ending the fight 1:55 into the round.
 
"When I landed that first big shot, I knew how hard it was,‚Äù said Murtazaliev. ‚ÄúTszyu is a real warrior and I hope one day we can work together and spar and help each other to grow."
 
"Every time I step into the ring I leave it all in there,‚Äù said Tszyu. ‚ÄúThings didn't go to plan and the better man won tonight. No excuses. After the first shot, things started not going according to plan. That's part of boxing, you get hit and reactions get slower. Bakhram is the man at 154."

#MurtazalievTszyu #TimTszyu #Murtazaliev

snippet.title: JJ Redick Delivered A Coaching MASTERCLASS On Opening Night
snippet.description:
RateGame Android: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.rategamemobile&pcampaignid=web_share

RateGame iOS: https://apps.apple.com/app/apple-store/id6477869711?pt=126905374&ct=HeatCheckRegSzn24-25&mt=8

Opening night was a real spectacle and despite all the hype being around the father and son duo, I was most intrigued by JJ Reddick and his offensive tricks.
First play of the game you already see the motion in the offense, with Lebron setting a good screen on the wing the diving hard to the basket, which forces Gobert to rotate, and from there the ball movement to the corner, and a swing to Hachimura‚Ä¶
And the very next play Rui exploded‚Ä¶
His phenomenal start was further emphasized on the defensive end. Watch the activity helping on the Randle back down and then the great recovery‚Ä¶
The Lakers defense led to another Lebron bucket and this time, it was a way better finish.
But despite the highlights, and the crowd going crazy, Minnesota managed to keep up with the Lakers, led by Anthony Edwards with 8 first quarter points, and he showed the crowd some of his flash.
Second quarter comes along and you see the 2-3 zone that the Wolves are in, but check out D‚ÄôAngelo Russel literally sneaking his way to the middle of the zone, forcing a response from the back line, and delivering a fantastic pass to the cutting Hayes for the dunk.
Then, moments later Reddick runs horns with the sharpshooter Knecht on the weak side. And watch him take off setting a back screen for Lebron, clearing out the perimeter for a handoff and a screen for himself. Reid has to come out and contest it, so this split second of help allows Hayes to cut inside, and the great pass by Knecht for the throwdown.
The next possession it‚Äôs almost the exact same thing with Dalton screening again for Lebron of the ball and sprinting out around the Jackson Hayes pick and this time, the defender is trailing him so he can fire away from downtown‚Ä¶
These terrific offensive possessions would spark a 27-6 run by the Lakers, sending the arena into delirium.
And this built enough of a cushion for Bronny to come into the game in a historic moment.
And he had his 1 chance for a bucket‚Ä¶
He couldn‚Äôt hit this one for the fans, but senior sure gave them something to cheer for.
The Lakers are up by 13 at the half, and JJ starts off the second half with some more motion into the offense.
Austin Reeves runs across 2 picks on the so-called Iverson cut, and Lebron follows, setting a hybrid between a screen and a slip, which creates hesitation for the defense, and at this moment he is obviously open for the bounce pass, which creates a 2 on 1 between him AD and Gobert. So it‚Äôs a perfect execution as we let it roll, for a beautiful alley oop dunk.
Thing is, it was mostly AD for the Lakers in this quarter. On both ends of the court.
And despite a terrific quarter of 13 points and 5 rebounds, Minnesota started to get into a rhythm and went on a mini run towards the end.
This gave me hope for an exciting finish but maaan, Anthony Davis went god mode in the 4th and he was not going to let the Lakers lose on opening night.
36 points, 16 rebounds, 4 assists and 3 blocks a blockbuster performance from AD.
I gave this game a 6.6 on Rate Game which was obviously lower than what Lakers fans rated it.
And if you‚Äôre new around here, Rate Game is an app that I‚Äôm a part of, made for the real fans of the game.
In a world polluted by betting and gambling, Rate Game is a pure diary where you keep track of what games you watched and which ones were the best. I watch a ton of games every season so this is great for me to look back on. We now have a hide scores feature so you can only see the ratings and decide which game to watch in the morning based on the scores. This feature is gamechanger.
I‚Äôm on here every night so join me to see what I‚Äôm watching and to post what you saw . The new design is sick, and we now have all the major US sports along with the Premier League Soccer and NCAA action. Click the link in the description for iOS or Android.
Moving on to ring night in Boston where it was all smiles before the game. I, on the other hand, had high hopes for my brand new Knicks. Boy I had no idea what I was in for.
First play of the game we got the high screen for Tatum and Towns is not willing to commit all the way and risk getting blown by. So JT gets a practice shot and he swishes it.
The high big men screens would be the Knicks nemesis, as we see another one here and the great maneuver by Kornet to switch the side at the last second, fooling the defender and opening up another shot for Tatum for another three.
JT said during preseason that he was tinkering with his shot, and some bozo made a youtube video doubting him. Of course then he responds with a 15 point first quarter going 4 for 6 from downtown. This opened up a barrage of threes by the Celtics, collectively going 10 for 17 from long range in the opening period alone.

Wayne Colley, better known as ‚ÄúKountry Wayne‚Äù, is not your average skit-standup comedian. If you asked him to describe himself, he would say he is just a reserved vegan and father of eight who wants what‚Äôs best for his kids. Hailing from Millen, Georgia, Wayne grew up with aspirations of becoming a super-star rapper, but those ambitions quickly changed when he posted a video to Facebook and became a viral sensation overnight.
Wayne attacked his new found fame head on and grew his audience to over 10 Million followers across Facebook & Instagram by delivering liked content on a daily basis. With his humble roots and unbridled energy it‚Äôs clear Wayne will be making people laugh for years to come.

snippet.title: Racing Towards A MASSIVE 150ft Hill in 1000+ Horsepower Cars!  (KD Dragway)
snippet.description:
KD Dragway is unlike any other track with a massive 150 ft hill serving as the shut down. The track itself has a lot of character as well but even once you're through that you have to account for the change in elevation as you pass the finish line. Although sketchy, it does make for some seriously entertaining racing which we got to experience quite a bit of.

snippet.title: Love Hurts | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
You can‚Äôt break up with your past. 
#LoveHurtsMovie is in theaters February 7.
______ 
 
No matter how hard you try, you can‚Äôt break up with your past. 

This Valentine‚Äôs Day, Oscar¬Æ winner Ke Huy Quan (Everything Everywhere All at Once, Loki) rockets into his first major leading man role as an unlikely hero, a seemingly mild-mannered realtor with a dark secret that he is desperate to leave behind. Spoiler alert: He won‚Äôt. 

From 87North‚Äîproducers of the groundbreaking action films Nobody, Violent Night, Bullet Train, Atomic Blonde and The Fall Guy‚Äîcomes a visceral, high-octane story of wrath and revenge.  

Quan stars as Marvin Gable, a realtor working the Milwaukee suburbs, where ‚ÄòFor Sale‚Äô signs bloom. Gable receives a crimson envelope from Rose (Oscar¬Æ winner Ariana DeBose; West Side Story, Argylle), a former partner-in-crime that he had left for dead. She‚Äôs not happy. 

Now, Marvin is thrust back into a world of ruthless hitmen, filled with double-crosses and open houses turned into deadly warzones. With his brother Knuckles (Daniel Wu; Tomb Raider, Warcraft), a volatile crime lord, hunting him, Marvin must confront the choices that haunt him and the history he never truly buried.

The film features a killer soundtrack and impressive and diverse cast that includes former NFL running back and Super Bowl champion Marshawn ‚ÄúBeast Mode‚Äù Lynch (Bottoms, 80 for Brady), Mustafa Shakir (Emancipation, Luke Cage), Lio Tipton (Crazy, Stupid, Love., Lucy), Rhys Darby (Jumanji: The Next Level, Yes Man), Andr√© Eriksen (Violent Night, The Trip) and Sean Astin (The Lord of the Rings trilogy, Perry Mason).

Produced by 87North‚Äôs Kelly McCormick and David Leitch, Love Hurts is written by Matthew Murray (Sheltered, CloudStreet: Soaring the American West) & Josh Stoddard (Warrior, Kaleidoscope) and Luke Passmore (Archenemy, Slaughterhouse Rulez). Guy Danella (Violent Night) is also producing. The executive producer is Ben Ormand. 
 
Making his feature film directing debut on Love Hurts is acclaimed veteran stunt coordinator and fight coordinator JoJo Eusebio, whose credits include some of the greatest action films of the past decade including Black Panther, The Avengers, the John Wick films, The Matrix Resurrections, Violent Night, The Fall Guy and Deadpool 2. Eusebio also served as the second-unit director on Deadpool 2, Violent Night and Birds of Prey.

snippet.title: One Vs World Challenge - Pro Skyrim Exploiter Hunted by EVERYTHING
snippet.description:
Play War Thunder now with my link, and get a massive, free bonus pack including vehicles, boosters and more: https://playwt.link/thespiffingbrit24

War Thunder is a highly detailed vehicle combat game containing over 2000 playable tanks, aircrafts and ships spanning over 100 years of development. Immerse yourself completely in dynamic battles with an unparalleled combination of realism and approachability.

Welcome to my skyrim One vs World Challenge! Today I will be using a custom mod developed for me by the incredible RedxYeti (https://next.nexusmods.com/profile/RedxYeti/mods) in this modpack every living creature in the world of skyrim from the smallest rabbit to the largest giant will not stop till they have hunted us down and defeated us. I am playing on legendary survival difficulty and have just 5 days to collect 5 items. Each death slows me down massively so in this incredibly impossible world can the spiffing brit still exploit his way to victory and win?

Join this channel to get access to perks:

snippet.title: Inside Sabrina Carpenter‚Äôs ‚ÄòShort n' Sweet‚Äô Tour Looks | Vogue
snippet.description:
While getting ready for her hometown show in Philadelphia, Sabrina Carpenter and stylist Jared Ellner break down all the looks they‚Äôve come up with for Sabrina's "Short n' Sweet" tour. Sabrina and Jared consistently mine the past for inspiration, incorporating babydoll dresses reminiscent of Brigitte Bardot and 1960s fashion, Marilyn Monroe-inspired catsuits, and ABBA-esque skirts. The show, which emulates everything from a morning bath to a date-night evening, unfolds over the course of a fictional day. With outfit changes in three acts featuring designs from Victoria‚Äôs Secret, Patou, and Ludovic de Saint Sernin, the wardrobe plays alongside the concert's central conceit, evolving as time unfurls.

snippet.title: Masahiro Sakurai on Creating Games: Finale Special
snippet.description:
For the special finale episode, I'll be discussing the ins and outs of the creation of this channel. I'll talk about why I'm wrapping things up, and maybe even share some surprising info along the way?
By the way, this episode will fall under the Game Concepts category, since I use that category as a space to discuss the ideas behind my various works. Of course, this one's not an actual game, but on my Japanese channel this category is called "Project Concepts"‚Äîso it's not strictly restricted to games, after all!
---
Though my final video's been released, the channel itself won't be going anywhere. I hope it can serve as a study guide of sorts for those already in the game industry and for those aspiring to join it.

Additionally, I expect I'll be using this channel again at some point to share announcements or maybe upload something a little more laid-back. Whatever the case, I hope our paths cross again soon!
